IMPRESSION/REPORT/PLAN
#1 Biopsy-proven recurrent rectal cancer from the vagina
Ms. Kent is referred for further evaluation and treatment of recurrent rectal cancer.  This is biopsy-proven from the vagina and likely involves her rectal stump.  Discussed with her the need for restaging CT chest, abdomen and pelvis and will obtain chest x-ray, lab work and ECG for purposes of anesthesia.  Patient will then meet with Dr. Elvira Wegman from colon and rectal surgery for surgical recommendations, followed with Dr. Jean Knox for consideration of intraoperative radiation therapy.  She has had complications from her previous radiation therapy of an enterocutaneous fistula which has subsequently resolved, a persistent rectovaginal fistula and a persistent abscess.  Patient will likely need to meet with stoma therapy at some point as well.  I provided her with prescriptions for Lyrica and MS-Contin along with renewal of her oxycodone for immediately release for pain control.  Examination under anesthesia may be most appropriate in assessing this woman's disease.
Discussed with Dr. Blanca Schaffer, note to follow.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.

